<subSubSection id="C34C655AFFB5534527DAF7FF5C4FB3B8" pageId="4" pageNumber="435" type="distribution">
<caption id="DF296659FFB5534527DAF7FF5C4FB3B8" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6585536" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6585536" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6585536/files/figure.png" inLine="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="435" targetBox="[126,716,1989,2403]" targetPageId="4">
<paragraph id="8BE936D1FFB5534527DAF7FF5C4FB3B8" blockId="4.[739,1330,1979,2405]" pageId="4" pageNumber="435">
<emphasis id="B922EAC3FFB5534527DAF7FF5CAAB308" bold="true" box="[740,916,2136,2169]" pageId="4" pageNumber="435">Distribution.</emphasis>
NW Argentina, in the highlands of Salta, Catamarca, and Tucuman provinces.
</paragraph>
</caption>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C34C655AFFB5534527DBF7695FF7B2C8" pageId="4" pageNumber="435" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BE936D1FFB5534527DBF7695FF7B2C8" blockId="4.[739,1330,1979,2405]" lastBlockId="4.[127,1333,2413,3000]" pageId="4" pageNumber="435">
<emphasis id="B922EAC3FFB5534527DBF7695CD6B39E" bold="true" box="[741,1000,2254,2287]" pageId="4" pageNumber="435">Descriptive notes.</emphasis>
Head-body 186 mm (maximum 220 mm), ear 17 mm, hindfoot 37 mm; weight 150-220 g. Shipton’s Mountain Cavy is a small cavy. Back is dull brown to tawny, and venter is buffy white or whitish. Ears are short with fine buffy hairs.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C34C655AFFB553452541F61B5BA1B2AC" box="[127,1183,2492,2525]" pageId="4" pageNumber="435" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph id="8BE936D1FFB553452541F61B5BA1B2AC" blockId="4.[127,1333,2413,3000]" box="[127,1183,2492,2525]" pageId="4" pageNumber="435">
<emphasis id="B922EAC3FFB553452541F61B5FD0B2AC" bold="true" box="[127,238,2492,2525]" pageId="4" pageNumber="435">Habitat.</emphasis>
Andean and pre-Andean shrublands at elevations of 3000-4500 m.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C34C655AFFB5534525BEF6445C3EB15C" pageId="4" pageNumber="435" type="food_feeding">
<paragraph id="8BE936D1FFB5534525BEF6445C3EB15C" blockId="4.[127,1333,2413,3000]" pageId="4" pageNumber="435">
<emphasis id="B922EAC3FFB5534525BEF6445EBDB175" bold="true" box="[128,387,2531,2564]" pageId="4" pageNumber="435">Food and Feeding.</emphasis>
There is no specific information available for this species, but Shipton’s Mountain Cavy is no doubt herbivorous.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C34C655AFFB5534525BEF5945CFBB125" box="[128,965,2611,2644]" pageId="4" pageNumber="435" type="breeding">
